<P>
CRASH KILLS WOMAN IN SIGHT OF FAMILY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman was killed Thursday when the car she was driving went out of control 
and flipped on the southbound Hollywood Freeway near Strathern Street in North 
Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
Maria Ramirez, 26, of North Hollywood died at the scene of the 2:30 p.m. 
accident, California Highway Patrol Officer Bob Weaver said. 
</P>
<P>
Ramirez was attempting to move into the a left lane when she noticed another 
car moving into that lane from her left. She swerved too abruptly and her car 
flipped, landing upside down on an embankment, Weaver said. 
</P>
<P>
Members of Ramirez' family were traveling in another vehicle two cars behind 
her when the accident occurred, Weaver said. 
