<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MOORPARK KEEPS STREAKS ALIVE, 9-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moorpark College kept three streaks alive with a 9-0 Western State Conference 
softball victory Thursday over Cuesta at Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
It marked the Lady Raiders' 23rd conference victory in a row, their 38th 
consecutive conference home victory and kept them unscored upon in conference 
games this season. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark has outscored seven WSC opponents, 51-0. 
</P>
<P>
Sophomore De Dow improved her record to 17-6 by pitching a one-hitter. She 
struck out four and walked two. 
</P>
<P>
Missy Cress paced Moorpark's 13-hit attack with a triple and double and two 
runs batted in. 
</P>
<P>
Chris Singer hit her third home run of the season and Jamie McDaniel smacked 
her first. 
</P>
<P>
In another softball game: 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran 10-6, Redlands 2-3 -- Dana Sangster pitched a four-hitter to win 
the first game and Leslie Stevens pitched a three-hitter to win the second game 
for Cal Lutheran in a nonconference doubleheader at Redlands. 
</P>
<P>
Michelle Campos had a three-run triple in the fifth inning of the first game 
for Cal Lutheran (19-12). 
</P>
<P>
In the second game, DeAndra Pilkington was two for four and teammate Teri Rupe 
hit a two-run home run. 
</P>
<P>
BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
Pierce 7, Santa Monica 6 -- With Pierce trailing, 6-4, in the bottom of the 
ninth, pinch-hitter Bobby Weer tripled in Kevin Johnson and Billy Morris. 
</P>
<P>
Tony Jordan then singled home Weer, giving Pierce (13-13, 6-5 in conference 
play) a WSC victory at home. 
</P>
<P>
Pierce's Louis Birdt pitched eight innings, allowing 12 hits and six earned 
runs while striking out seven. 
</P>
<P>
College of the Canyons 9, Santa Barbara 5 -- Randy Cooper hit a three-run homer 
in the second inning as Canyons (15-12, 8-3) pulled away early in a WSC game at 
Canyons. 
</P>
<P>
Canyons' Alan Sedacca (2-0) pitched eight innings, striking out six and 
allowing three earned runs on eight hits. 
</P>
<P>
The Cougars' Scott Roth was two for three with an RBI and Gary Morgan was two 
for four as Canyons racked up 11 hits. 
</P>
<P>
Moorpark 15, Cuesta 6 -- Moorpark scored four runs in the seventh and six in 
the eighth to snap a 4-4 tie in the WSC game at Cuesta. Craig Pearson was three 
for four for Moorpark (19-9, 8-3), raising his average to .531 (25 for 47) in 
conference play. Steve Sisco was three for five. 
</P>
<P>
Todd Gerbovaz (4-2) struck out four and yielded two earned runs through 6 1/3 
innings. 
</P>
<P>
El Camino 13, Valley 10 -- Steve Slattery was rocked for 11 runs in the first 
three innings and the Monarchs never recovered in a nonconference game at El 
Camino. 
</P>
<P>
Trailing, 13-4, after seven innings, Valley scored two runs in the eighth and 
four in the ninth to make it close. 
</P>
<P>
E. J. Pape had three hits, including his ninth home run of the season -- a 
two-run shot in the fourth -- and three RBIs for Valley (21-6-1) and teammate 
John Stephens added a three-run triple in the ninth. 
</P>
<P>
Mission 9, Compton 8 -- Albert Torres drove in the winning run in the ninth 
inning with a sacrifice fly to center field, giving Mission (7-16, 5-7) a 
Southern California Athletic Conference victory at home. Mission pitcher Jose 
Garcia (5-5) went the distance, scattering 10 hits and striking out 13. 
</P>
<P>
Manuel Orozco was two for five with three RBIs and Robert Bradford, who singled 
to lead off the ninth before being pulled for pinch-runner, also had two hits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
