<P>
VETS BACK FROM VISIT WITH EX-FOES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A group of Vietnam veterans returned from Southeast Asia on Thursday to an 
airport greeting of confetti and hugs and kisses. 
</P>
<P>
"Boy, we didn't get a greeting like this when we came back from the war," said 
Army veteran Steve Brooks of Santa Cruz. 
</P>
<P>
While in Vietnam, the veterans helped build a 14-room clinic for their former 
enemies, using $50,000 in donated money. 
</P>
<P>
With the cooperation of the Vietnamese government, the veterans, along with 
about 30 Vietnamese, erected a one-story, 2,500-square-foot building at Vung 
Tau, 60 miles from Ho Chi Minh City, formerly Saigon. 
