<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALL-STAR HIGH SCHOOL TEAMS PLAY TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The sixth annual Southern California All-Star high school basketball 
doubleheader, matching girls' and boys' teams from the City against those from 
the Southern Section, will be played tonight at Cal State Dominguez Hills, 
starting at 6:30. 
</P>
<P>
The City boys' team will be led by Terry Cannon of Crenshaw, the City 4-A 
Division player of the year, and Brent Lofton of Woodland Hills El Camino Real. 
Heading the Southern Section team will be three Division I first-team 
selections -- Brian Camper of Lakewood, Malru Dottin of Santa Ana Saddleback 
and Corey Rogers of La Puente Nogales. 
</P>
<P>
The City girls' team will be led by Valerie Agee of Palisades, a two-time 
All-City selection, and Claudia Jones of Crenshaw, who led the Cougars to the 
City 4-A finals. Leading the Southern Section team will be Heidi and Heather 
Burge of Palos Verdes, two-time Southern Section selections; Joni Easterly of 
Anaheim Katella, and Kim Gessig of Upland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
