</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kraft Ordered to Halt Cheese Ads: A Federal Trade Commission judge ordered 
Kraft Inc. to stop misrepresenting the nutrient content of its cheese slices, 
ruling the company "falsely advertised" that they contain as much calcium as 5 
ounces of milk and more calcium than most imitation slices. The judge said a 
3/4 ounce slice of Kraft Singles has 70% of the calcium of 5 ounces of whole 
milk and less than 68.2% of the calcium of 5 ounces of low-fat or skim milk. 
Parker also ruled that virtually all imitation cheese slices contain the same 
amount of calcium as Kraft Singles. 
</P>
