EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Maxwell Communication Corp.: The British conglomerate that last year acquired 
Macmillan Inc. said 1988 profit rose 2.9% to $230.5 million from the year 
before. Sales climbed 27% to $1.9 billion. In addition to the $2.6-billion 
takeover of Macmillan, Maxwell Communication reached agreement in October with 
U.S. publisher Dun &amp; Bradstreet to buy the Official Airlines Guide. 
