<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: HUNTINGTON BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
FIRE DESTROYS MOBILE HOME; $75,000 LOSS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A mobile home and its contents were destroyed by fire Thursday causing an 
estimated $75,000 in damage, according to county fire controller Colleen Keith. 
</P>
<P>
Firefighters were called to Driftwood Mobile Home Park, 21462 Pacific Coast 
Highway, at 3:52 p.m. after a neighbor reported smoke coming from the trailer, 
Keith said. Eleven fire companies responded to the blaze. 
</P>
<P>
Randall Reed Anaple, the occupant, was not at home at the time of the fire. 
There were no injuries. Cause of the fire is under investigation, Keith said. 
</P>
