<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PREPS; 
</P>
<P>
TRACK AND FIELD ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
A.J. YATES ENJOYS FIELD DAY FOR LOS ALAMITOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A.J. Yates won two events and anchored two winning relay teams to lead Los 
Alamitos High School to a 70-65 victory over Loara Thursday in an Empire League 
boys' track and field meet at Loara. 
</P>
<P>
The meet came down to the last event, the mile relay, and Yates, running the 
anchor leg, held off Loara for the victory. Yates won the 100-yard dash (10.3 
seconds) and the 220 (23.3) and anchored the Griffins' 440 relay (45.7) and the 
mile relay (3:40.7). 
</P>
<P>
Greg Ramsey won the high jump (6-6), the high hurdles (15.4), the 330-yard 
hurdles (42.5) and the triple jump (41-6) for Loara. 
</P>
<P>
In Empire League girls' track and field: 
</P>
<P>
Loara 67 1/2, Los Alamitos 60 1/2 -- Kelly Graton won the high jump (5-7 1/2), 
the high hurdles (15.5), the intermediate hurdles (50.5) and contributed to the 
winning 440 relay team (52.1) to lead Loara at home. 
</P>
<P>
In Angelus League boys' track and field: 
</P>
<P>
Mater Dei 73 1/2, St. Francis 47 1/2 -- Jason Uhl put the shot 50 feet 6 inches 
to win the event for Mater Dei at home. 
</P>
<P>
In Century League boys' track and field: 
</P>
<P>
El Modena 96 2/3, Santa Ana 39 1/3 -- Robbie Pietsch won the 330 hurdles (42.1) 
and the 120 high hurdles (15.6), and Ray Vansluis won the pole vault (13-0) and 
the long jump (19-7) to lead El Modena (2-0 in league) at Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
In Century League girls' track and field: 
</P>
<P>
El Modena 81, Santa Ana 40 -- Jenni Moore won the 330 hurdles (49.9) and the 
110 hurdles (16.8) to lead El Modena (1-1 in league) at Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
In Century League girls' track and field: 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 68, Santa Ana Valley 59 -- Allison Franke won the discus (147-1), the 
triple jump (35-10) and the 100-meter hurdles (15.4) for host Canyon. Sheila 
Green won the long jump (17-1) and was second in the triple jump (35-0 3/4) for 
Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
In Garden Grove League boys' track and field: 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 77, Los Amigos 54 -- Mike Moore won the 100-yard dash (10.0) and 220 
(23.7) for Kennedy at Los Amigos. Charlie Cummings won the triple jump (44-0) 
and Brian Cline the high jump (6-3) for the Fighting Irish. 
</P>
<P>
In Orange League boys' track and field: 
</P>
<P>
Magnolia 84, Brea-Olinda 44 -- Phouphet Singbandith won the high jump (6-2), 
the long jump (21-7) and the triple jump (47-7 1/2) to lead Magnolia at home. 
</P>
<P>
Valencia 94, Western 42 -- Kevin Thomas won 100-yard dash (9.9) and 220 (22.7) 
