<HEADLINE>
<P>
SADDLEBACK GAME SUSPENDED AFTER BRAWL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Saddleback College's baseball game against Riverside was suspended in the ninth 
inning Thursday after a bench-clearing brawl that lasted approximately five 
minutes, according to Saddleback assistant coach Charley Phillips. 
</P>
<P>
The fight started with two outs in the top of the ninth inning and Saddleback 
leading, 8-3, at Riverside. 
</P>
<P>
The brawl began after Saddleback outfielder Justin Pysar was pushed to the 
ground after being tagged out in a rundown between first and second, Saddleback 
Coach Rich Rommel said. 
</P>
<P>
Both benches cleared and Saddleback's Larry Maddox punched Jackie Jempson, 
Phillips said. 
</P>
<P>
Maddox, Jempson and a second Riverside player were ejected and the umpires 
suspended the game. All three players will be suspended for one game, Rommel 
said. 
</P>
