<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
CADUFF, WACHTER WIN GIANT SLALOMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SHIGA KOGEN, Japan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Daniel Caduff edged fellow Swiss skier Peter Mueller in the men's super giant 
slalom today, and Austrian Anita Wachter easily took the women's event in the 
Lark Sports World International Grand Prix. 
</P>
<P>
The two won the men's and women's downhill races in the same meet on Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Caduff skied down the 8,415-foot Mt. Higashidate Super-G course in central 
Japan in 1 minute, 47.23 seconds, against Mueller's 1:47.40. The course had a 
vertical drop of 2,145 feet and 54 gates. Austrian Willibald Zechner came in 
third in 1:49.51. 
</P>
<P>
In the women's race, over a 42-gate, 6,930-foot course, Wachter, the lone 
foreign entry, finished in 1 minute, 31.85 seconds, nearly six seconds ahead of 
Japan's Kana Kawashima, who was timed in 1:37.67. 
</P>
</TEXT>
