<P>
WOMAN TO HEAD ALOHA BOWL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HONOLULU 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marcia Cherner has been named president and executive director of the Aloha 
Bowl, becoming the first woman executive director of a sanctioned NCAA bowl 
game. She has been involved in the Aloha Bowl since it was founded in 1982, and 
previously was general manager. Cherner succeeds Mackey Yanagisawa, the founder 
of the bowl game, who will remain as chairman of the board. 
</P>
