IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
AMERICAN MARATHON TEAM NAMED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
INDIANAPOLIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four men and four women have been selected to represent the United States at 
the International Amateur Athletic Federation World Cup marathon at Milan, 
Italy, next week. 
</P>
<P>
The men's roster consists of Jim Hage of Lanham, Md.; Gary Gargasz, Volant, 
Pa.; Chriss James, Salt Lake City, and Bob Hensley, Port St. Lucie, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
The women chosen were Sue Marchiano, Henderson, Nev.; Jane Welzel, 
Northeastern, Mass.; Gordon Bloch, New York, and Charlotte Thomas, San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
The women's race will be held April 15 and the men's event April 16. 
</P>
